The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 14 September is 320,380 (569.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 September, there were 18,211 new confirmed cases (32.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 September, there were 11,819 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 54% (6392 extra cases).
